                    <h2>IMS Policy</h2>
                </div>

                <div class="ims-body">

                    <!-- Policy Content -->
                    <div class="ims-content">

                        <p>TKIL Industries Pvt. Ltd. offers engineering, procurement, construction, and service of plants and machinery to domestic and overseas markets. We are committed to providing products and services conforming to high quality, safety, health and environmental standards that are cost effective and meet the needs and expectations of all relevant interested parties.</p>

                        <p>Integrated Management System has been established and is being implemented and maintained in accordance with the requirements of current editions of respective International Standards. With a view to update and maintain the system to changing requirement of business, customers and applicable standards, improvement actions are implemented by determining and managing risks and opportunities. IMS Objectives along with Energy performance indicators are reviewed periodically and set with targets to align with current business need and priorities.</p>

                        <p>We are committed that every employee receives necessary training, information, instructions and is responsible to comply with the established Integrated Management System, applicable legal, statutory and other requirements to which the Organization subscribes. Consultation and participation of employees and stakeholders, whenever necessary, is encouraged at relevant stages during implementation to enhance performance of the Integrated Management System.</p>

                        <p>It is our endeavor to minimize the adverse impact of our activities, products and services by protecting the environment, including prevention of pollution and responsible use of resources, eliminating hazards and reducing OH&amp;S risks by adopting safe work practices and technologies, and providing adequate supervision to enhance employee wellbeing and promote, mitigation and control of any injury, ill health and environmental damage due to our operations.</p>

                        <p>We strive to prioritize energy efficiency, responsible energy use, and enhance the usage of clean energy sources. This encompasses the design for optimal energy efficiency, monitoring energy performance, setting improvement targets, engaging employees in energy conservation, and procurement of energy efficient products.</p>

                        <p>We are committed to continually improve effectiveness of the Integrated Management System with an intent to enhance customer satisfaction and promote sustainability of Divisions.</p>

                        <p>Top Management is accountable for development, application and effectiveness of the Integrated Management System and provides support and resources to all employees for its effective implementation.</p>

                    </div>

                    <!-- Signature Strip -->
